! Interactive Clusters

Drag nodes onto each other to group them visually. Each graph stores its cluster config independently.

<$graph physics="no">
<$properties.persistent $dataTiddler="$:/state/demo/cluster-positions">
<$properties $for="graph" clusterData="$:/state/demo/clusters">
<$properties $for="nodes" color="SteelBlue" size="20">

  <$node $tiddler="demo:alice" label="Alice" $pos=<<pos>>/>
  <$node $tiddler="demo:bob" label="Bob" $pos=<<pos>>/>
  <$node $tiddler="demo:carol" label="Carol" $pos=<<pos>>/>
  <$node $tiddler="demo:dave" label="Dave" $pos=<<pos>>/>
  <$node $tiddler="demo:eve" label="Eve" $pos=<<pos>> color="Crimson"/>
  <$node $tiddler="demo:frank" label="Frank" $pos=<<pos>> color="DarkGoldenRod"/>

  <$edge $from="demo:alice" $to="demo:bob"/>
  <$edge $from="demo:bob" $to="demo:carol"/>
  <$edge $from="demo:carol" $to="demo:dave"/>
  <$edge $from="demo:dave" $to="demo:eve"/>
  <$edge $from="demo:eve" $to="demo:frank"/>
  <$edge $from="demo:alice" $to="demo:eve" stroke="dashed"/>

</$properties>
</$properties>
</$properties.persistent>
</$graph>

!! Try it

# ''Drag Alice onto Bob'' → creates "Cluster #1" containing both
# ''Drag Carol onto the cluster'' → adds her to the group
# ''Double-click'' the cluster label → rename it (e.g. "Team A")
# ''Double-click'' again → pick a color from the palette
# ''Drag a node far away'' (200+ px from where you grabbed it) → removes it from the cluster
# ''Drag one cluster onto another'' → nests them

!! How it works

Clusters are named visual groups — not tiddlers. They're stored as JSON in the config tiddler (`$:/state/demo/clusters`). Each graph can have its own config.

|!Gesture |!Effect |
|Drag node → node |Create cluster |
|Drag node → cluster |Add to cluster |
|Drag 200+ px |Remove from cluster |
|Double-click label |Rename + color |
|Drag cluster → cluster |Nest clusters |
|Remove all members |Auto-delete cluster |

